It’s always going to be Me vs Me . A lot of times we like to compare our self to others . “ why couldn’t that be me ?“ ,””How come I didn’t get that opportunity? “ “When is it going to be my time ?  The sooner you understand and accept that nothing happens on “Your time “ but on Gods time the easier it’ll be for you . So the trick for all my success is God with a side of consistent work and dedication .your faith have to be stronger than anything .Everyone can give up  on you at anytime but you can’t give up on your self .

PSA ..My bf was excited he’s just very chill and laid back( yes people like that exist ) . Next time I’ll make sure to tell him to jump in the air ,drop in a split and shout for his next surprise 😂

Crazy what almost 30 pound difference can do 😅.As we start the new year I challenge you to set standards for yourself starting with your health . Setting these standards for yourselves helps you hold your self accountable.. You can’t have standards for you relationship ,your business but not your health .  Start holding yourself accountable!

My goal was to lose this weight before my bf birthday (Dec 5)and look like a new person by 2024 and I did it 🥰 .i gave  myself 2  and a half months starting the end of September .i was tired of complaining about my weight one minute but ordering chick fil A right after lmao  smh .everyday I’ll say “I’ll start next week “ then next week comes and I add another week then in a blink of eye months passed by .i know alot of y’all can relate lol . I knew I had serious discipline when I went to Bahamas for a friend bday and stuck to my “No alcohol for the next 3 months “rule . My friends were shocked ,I was taking water shots the whole trip .  Staying consistent and being discipline is how I was able to do it . Losing weight is more of a mental battle then it is physical so ask yourself are you gonna start now or are you going to start “next week”
